---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="About | Willy W."
  description="How Willy W. works with AI to build practical systems."
>
  <div class="page-hero">
    <p class="kicker">about</p>
    <h1>I use AI like a small engineering team, then make the work prove itself.</h1>
    <p>
      This page will hold the real bio after curation. For now, it sketches the working model:
      clear goals, tight feedback loops, and systems that earn trust through checks.
    </p>
  </div>

  <section aria-labelledby="work-title">
    <div class="sec-head">
      <h2 id="work-title">How I work with AI</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="page-card">
      <p>
        Claude helps shape the architecture and review the result. Codex turns the plan into
        working code. Obsidian keeps the durable memory so each pass starts with context.
      </p>
      <div class="pipe">
        claude <span>(architect/review)</span> &rarr; codex <span>(build)</span> &rarr;
        obsidian <span>(memory)</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="background-title">
    <div class="sec-head">
      <h2 id="background-title">Background</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="page-card">
      <p>
        The finished version will be specific and approved before publishing. The placeholder
        version keeps the point simple: I learn by building, write down decisions, and keep
        the evidence close to the work.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
